<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="1254" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1254">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.63/482</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Ambassador <persName type="to">Fletcher</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 377</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-27">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 27, 1917</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to Mr. Summerlin’s telegram No.
                                342,<note n="2" xml:id="d1254fn2">Not printed.</note> of July 30,
                            1917, 4 p.m., reporting that a new mining law containing no radical
                            features was being prepared by the Mexican Minister of Industry and
                            Commerce and would probably be submitted to the Congress at its regular
                            session, you are instructed to furnish the Department with a copy of the
                            new law as soon as it can be obtained.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Frank L. Polk</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>